1.name: Bulbasaur
1.info:
While it is young, it uses the nutrients that are
stored in the seed on its back in order to grow.

2.name: Ivysaur
2.info:
Exposure to sunlight adds to its strength.
Sunlight also makes the bud on its back
grow larger.

3.name: Venusaur
3.info:
A bewitching aroma wafts from its flower.
The fragrance becalms those engaged
in a battle.

4.name: Charmander
4.info:
From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip
of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to
go out.

5.name: Charmeleon
5.info:
If it becomes agitated during battle, it spouts
intense flames, incinerating its surroundings.

6.name: Charizard
6.info:
Its wings can carry this Pokémon close to an
altitude of 4,600 feet. It blows out fire at very
high temperatures.

7.name: Squirtle
7.info:
When it feels threatened, it draws its limbs inside
its shell and sprays water from its mouth.

8.name: Wartortle
8.info:
It cleverly controls its furry ears and tail to
maintain its balance while swimming.

9.name: Blastoise
9.info:
The rocket cannons on its shell fire jets of water
capable of punching holes through thick steel.

10.name: Caterpie
10.info:
Il suo corpo è molle e privo di forza.
Molto spesso il suo destino in natura è
di cadere preda di altri Pokémon.

11.name: Metapod
11.info:
Its hard shell doesn’t crack a bit even if Pikipek
pecks at it, but it will tip over, spilling out
its insides.

12.name: Butterfree
12.info:
Nectar from pretty flowers is its favorite food.
In fields of flowers, it has heated battles with
Cutiefly for territory.

19.name: Rattata
19.info:
Un Pokémon muy extendido con el que conviene
tener cuidado ya que sus afilados incisivos son
capaces de roer maderas nobles sin problema.

20.name: Raticate
20.info:
Its whiskers are essential for maintaining its
balance. No matter how friendly you are, it will
get angry and bite you if you touch its whiskers.

21.name: Spearow
21.info:
Due to its short wings, it can’t fly long
distances. It wanders about restlessly and
pecks at bug Pokémon.

22.name: Fearow
22.info:
In Alola, fish Pokémon are its prey. It can be
seen circling above the ocean searching
for food.

23.name: Ekans
23.info:
The older it gets, the longer it grows. At night, it
wraps its long body around tree branches to rest.

24.name: Arbok
24.info:
The frightening patterns on its belly have been
studied. Six variations have been confirmed.

25.name: Pikachu
25.info:
While sleeping, it generates electricity in the
sacs in its cheeks. If it’s not getting enough
sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.

26.name: Raichu
26.info:
Because so many Trainers like the way Pikachu
looks, you don’t see this Pokémon very often.

27.name: Sandshrew
27.info:
When its skin gets wrinkled from moisture, it
heads for a volcano. It lies flat on a spot with a
lot of geothermal heat and dries itself out.

28.name: Sandslash
28.info:
Thanks to its thick claws, it’s good at climbing
trees. There are plenty of Sandslash that park
themselves in trees and go right to sleep.

29.name: Nidoran-f
29.info:
It uses its hard incisor teeth to crush and eat
berries. The tip of a female Nidoran’s horn is a
bit more rounded than the tip of a male’s horn.

30.name: Nidorina
30.info:
If the group is threatened, these Pokémon will
band together to assault enemies with a chorus
of ultrasonic waves.

31.name: Nidoqueen
31.info:
It pacifies offspring by placing them in the gaps
between the spines on its back. The spines will
never secrete poison while young are present.

32.name: Nidoran-m
32.info:
Small but brave, this Pokémon will hold its
ground and even risk its life in battle to protect
the female it’s friendly with.

33.name: Nidorino
33.info:
It’s nervous and quick to act aggressively.
The potency of its poison increases along with
the level of adrenaline present in its body.

34.name: Nidoking
34.info:
Nidoking prides itself on its strength. It’s forceful
and spirited in battle, making use of its thick tail
and diamond-crushing horn.

35.name: Clefairy
35.info:
Bathed in moonlight, its wings glow faintly.
Without even flapping, Clefairy rises into the air,
where it dances around.

36.name: Clefable
36.info:
Nelle notti di luna piena si perde a fissare il
cielo. Secondo alcuni studiosi, pensa con
nostalgia alla sua casa lontana.

37.name: Vulpix
37.info:
Crea palle infuocate che usa con maestria per
catturare le prede. Se allenato fin da cucciolo,
si affeziona come un Pokémon Cagnolino.

38.name: Ninetales
38.info:
The flickering flames it spews from its mouth
leave its opponents hypnotized. Then, this
extremely intelligent Pokémon attacks.

39.name: Jigglypuff
39.info:
The songs they sing are totally different
depending on the region they live in. Some even
sound like they’re shouting!

40.name: Wigglytuff
40.info:
When it gets angry, it inhales with all its might,
and its body gradually inflates. Sometimes they
can grow 20 times larger!

41.name: Zubat
41.info:
Their skin is so thin that they’ll be burned if
sunlight hits them. When it gets cold out, they
gather together to warm one another’s bodies.

42.name: Golbat
42.info:
They can suck down over 10 ounces of blood in
one go. They have been known to drink so much
blood that they can no longer fly.

43.name: Oddish
43.info:
Durante el día, se agazapa en el frío subsuelo
huyendo del sol. La luz de la luna le hace crecer.

44.name: Gloom
44.info:
Lo que parece baba es realmente un néctar muy
pegajoso que se adhiere sin remisión al tocarlo.

45.name: Vileplume
45.info:
Je größer die Blütenblätter, desto mehr giftige
Pollen enthält die Blüte. Aber es ist auch umso
erschöpfter, da sein Kopf so schwer wird.

46.name: Paras
46.info:
The mushrooms, known as tochukaso, are
controlling the bug. Even if the bug bugs the
mushrooms, they tell it to bug off.

47.name: Parasect
47.info:
Its poisonous spores are also used in traditional
medicine. Apparently, spores produced in Alola
are not of very good quality.

50.name: Diglett
50.info:
Around their crops, farmers plant the kind of
tree that Diglett like to eat as a way of getting
Diglett to plow the fields for them.

51.name: Dugtrio
51.info:
Dugtrio’s heads are sleek and smooth and
incredibly hard. It can dig through any soil with
its headbutts.

52.name: Meowth
52.info:
It loves coins, so if you give it one, you can
make friends with Meowth easily. But it’s fickle,
so you can’t count on that friendship lasting.

53.name: Persian
53.info:
Un Pokémon de alto copete, objetivo primordial
de ladrones que quieren apoderarse de la joya
que luce en la frente.

54.name: Psyduck
54.info:
It has been found that its brain cells are
10 times more active when Psyduck is
experiencing a headache.

55.name: Golduck
55.info:
È un nuotatore provetto. Muovendo abilmente
la sua lunga coda, può nuotare ininterrottamente
per due giorni.

56.name: Mankey
56.info:
If one gets angry, all the others around it will
get angry, so silence is a rare visitor in a troop
of Mankey.

57.name: Primeape
57.info:
I vasi sanguigni del suo cervello sono più robusti
di quelli degli altri Pokémon e sono in grado di
resistere al suo stato di collera perpetua.

58.name: Growlithe
58.info:
It has lived alongside humans since ages ago.
Its bones have been found in excavations of
ruins from the Stone Age.

59.name: Arcanine
59.info:
There are so many old tales about them that
they’re called legendary Pokémon, but there are
way more of them around than you’d expect.

60.name: Poliwag
60.info:
The direction of the swirl on their stomachs
differs depending on where they live. Poliwag
aficionados can tell them apart at a glance.

61.name: Poliwhirl
61.info:
Its health suffers when its skin dries out, so be
sure to moisturize it diligently.

62.name: Poliwrath
62.info:
È dotato di muscoli vigorosi, sviluppatisi
grazie al nuoto. Con un pugno può mandare
in frantumi anche un grosso masso.

63.name: Abra
63.info:
It can read others’ minds and will teleport away
when danger approaches. You must clear your
mind if you want to catch it.

64.name: Kadabra
64.info:
It possesses strong mental capabilities, but its
psychic powers are halved when it’s not
holding a silver spoon.

65.name: Alakazam
65.info:
If it trusts someone deeply, it will let them have
one of its spoons. Anything you eat with that
spoon is apparently delicious.

66.name: Machop
66.info:
L’istinto lo spinge a preferire cibi ricchi
di nutrienti, in modo da poter sviluppare
i muscoli nel modo più efficiente.

67.name: Machoke
67.info:
A popular motif for sculptures, its incredibly
well-developed muscles have captured the
imagination of many an artist.

68.name: Machamp
68.info:
Grazie alle sue quattro braccia può attaccare
e difendersi allo stesso tempo. Si dice che sia
esperto di tutte le arti marziali del mondo.

72.name: Tentacool
72.info:
Its body is 99% water. The remaining 1%
contains the organ that makes its poison.

73.name: Tentacruel
73.info:
It communicates with others of its kind by
lighting up the red orbs on its head. When
the orbs are blinking, it’s a warning sign.

74.name: Geodude
74.info:
It uses both hands to climb precipitous cliffs.
People who see it in action have been known to
take up bouldering.

75.name: Graveler
75.info:
Si sposta rotolando lungo dirupi scoscesi.
Se finisce dentro a un fiume, viene colto dalla
disperazione e si fa esplodere.

76.name: Golem
76.info:
It detonates its own body. The power from
that explosion can propel it up steep mountain
paths with amazing speed.

77.name: Ponyta
77.info:
If you’ve been accepted by Ponyta, its burning
mane is mysteriously no longer hot to the touch.

78.name: Rapidash
78.info:
The fastest runner becomes the leader, and it
decides the herd’s pace and direction of travel.

79.name: Slowpoke
79.info:
Although their tails, which fall off naturally, can
easily be found lying around, they’re a precious
ingredient for cooking.

80.name: Slowbro
80.info:
Shellder, in its greed to suck out more and more
sweetness from Slowbro’s tail, has
metamorphosed into a spiral-shaped shell.

81.name: Magnemite
81.info:
Perhaps because electrical lines are often
buried these days, the number of Magnemite
attacks on power plants has increased.

82.name: Magneton
82.info:
When rain clouds form, many Magneton gather
in high places to wait for lightning to strike.

83.name: Farfetchd
83.info:
They use a plant stalk as a weapon, but not all
of them use it in the same way. Several distinct
styles of stalk fighting have been observed.

86.name: Seel
86.info:
Loves freezing-cold conditions.
Relishes swimming in a frigid climate
of around 14 degrees Fahrenheit.

87.name: Dewgong
87.info:
Its entire body is a snowy white. Unharmed by
even intense cold, it swims powerfully
in icy waters.

88.name: Grimer
88.info:
The wastewater coming from factories is clean
these days, so Grimer have nothing to eat.
They’re said to be on the verge of extinction.

89.name: Muk
89.info:
Essendo portatore di germi, è stato sempre
cacciato senza pietà. Per questo il numero di
esemplari si è ridotto drasticamente.

90.name: Shellder
90.info:
Even when its shell is closed, its tongue still
hangs out. If you give its tongue a good yank,
the shock will cause Shellder to open its shell.

91.name: Cloyster
91.info:
Slowpoke tails are its favorite food. It has even
been known to come up on land to look for
Slowpoke from time to time.

92.name: Gastly
92.info:
Poisonous gas comprises 95% of its body. It’s
said that the remaining 5% is made up of the
souls of those who died from the gas.

93.name: Haunter
93.info:
It’s dangerous to go outside alone on nights
when you’re feeling sad. Haunter will catch you,
and you won’t be able to go back home.

94.name: Gengar
94.info:
Even your home isn’t safe. Gengar will lurk in
whatever dark corner of a room it can find and
wait for its chance to catch its prey.

95.name: Onix
95.info:
It rapidly bores through the ground at 50 mph by
squirming and twisting its massive, rugged body.

96.name: Drowzee
96.info:
Addormenta le prede per mangiare i loro sogni.
Sembra che non gradisca gli incubi a causa del
loro sapore acido.

97.name: Hypno
97.info:
There are some Hypno that assist doctors with
patients who can’t sleep at night in hospitals.

98.name: Krabby
98.info:
If it senses danger approaching, it cloaks itself
with bubbles from its mouth so it will look bigger.

99.name: Kingler
99.info:
Its oversized claw is very powerful, but when it’s
not in battle, the claw just gets in the way.

102.name: Exeggcute
102.info:
Although they are the same size as other
Exeggcute, the ones produced in Alola are quite
heavy. Their shells are packed full.

103.name: Exeggutor
103.info:
Each of its three heads has its own thoughts.
When they want to go in different directions,
Exeggutor becomes unable to move.

104.name: Cubone
104.info:
It wears its mother’s skull on its head, so no
one knows what its bare face looks like.
However, it’s clear that it’s always crying.

105.name: Marowak
105.info:
They thump their bones rhythmically to
communicate among themselves. There are
nearly 50 different rhythmic patterns.

106.name: Hitmonlee
106.info:
The legs freely contract and stretch. The stretchy
legs allow it to hit a distant foe with a rising kick.

107.name: Hitmonchan
107.info:
Its punches slice the air. However, it seems to
need a short break after fighting for three minutes.

108.name: Lickitung
108.info:
Its tongue spans almost seven feet and moves
more freely than its forelegs. Its licks can
cause paralysis.

109.name: Koffing
109.info:
It adores polluted air. Some claim that Koffing
used to be more plentiful in the Galar region
than they are now.

110.name: Weezing
110.info:
It can’t suck in air quite as well as a Galarian
Weezing, but the toxins it creates are more
potent than those of its counterpart.

111.name: Rhyhorn
111.info:
It can remember only one thing at a time. Once it
starts rushing, it forgets why it started.

112.name: Rhydon
112.info:
Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of
living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

113.name: Chansey
113.info:
In passato è stato vittima di una caccia sfrenata
per le sue uova. Per questo motivo non sono
rimasti molti esemplari di questo Pokémon.

114.name: Tangela
114.info:
The vines of a Tangela have a distinct scent.
In some parts of Galar, Tangela vines are used
as herbs.

115.name: Kangaskhan
115.info:
Non bisogna avvicinarsi a un cucciolo che gioca
fuori dal marsupio: la madre è sempre nei
paraggi e vigila attenta su di lui.

116.name: Horsea
116.info:
They swim with dance-like motions and cause
whirlpools to form. Horsea compete to see which
of them can generate the biggest whirlpool.

117.name: Seadra
117.info:
Seadra’s mouth is slender, but its suction power
is strong. In an instant, Seadra can suck in food
that’s larger than the opening of its mouth.

118.name: Goldeen
118.info:
The way it swims along fluttering its dress-like
fins has earned it the name “princess of
the water.”

119.name: Seaking
119.info:
I maschi danzano sul letto dei fiumi cercando
di attirare l’attenzione delle femmine, che si
radunano attorno al miglior danzatore.

120.name: Staryu
120.info:
Le ferite non sono un problema per Staryu:
grazie alle sue eccellenti capacità rigenerative,
torna intero in mezza giornata.

121.name: Starmie
121.info:
It rotates its geometrically shaped body to swim
through the water. It always seems to be
sending out mysterious radio waves.

122.name: Mr-mime
122.info:
Always practicing its pantomime act.
It makes enemies believe something exists
that really doesn’t.

123.name: Scyther
123.info:
Some call it a ninja. Its movements—
imperceptibly quick—are sufficient to cleave
the air in two. It’s very popular in Alola.

124.name: Jynx
124.info:
Appears to move to a rhythm of its own, as if it
were dancing. It wiggles its hips as it walks.

125.name: Electabuzz
125.info:
While it’s often blamed for power outages, the
truth is the cause of outages is more often
an error on the part of the electric company.

126.name: Magmar
126.info:
The hotter the place, the better they feel.
Magmar in Alola are said to be hardier than
those in other areas.

127.name: Pinsir
127.info:
Although it’s tough, it can’t handle cold well.
When night falls, it buries itself in leafage
and sleeps.

128.name: Tauros
128.info:
The climate seems to be related to the reason
Tauros in Alola are a little calmer than those in
other regions.

129.name: Magikarp
129.info:
Thanks to their strong hold on life, dirty water
doesn’t bother them at all. They live in waters
all over the world!

130.name: Gyarados
130.info:
The energy from evolution stimulated its brain
cells strongly, causing it to become
very ferocious.

131.name: Lapras
131.info:
They’ve been so cherished that there’s now an
overabundance. The fish Pokémon population
has declined in waters with too many Lapras.

132.name: Ditto
132.info:
It transforms into whatever it sees. If the thing
it’s transforming into isn’t right in front of it,
Ditto relies on its memory—so sometimes it fails.

133.name: Eevee
133.info:
Its genes are easily influenced by its
surroundings. Even its face starts to look like
that of its Trainer.

134.name: Vaporeon
134.info:
It detects nearby moisture with its fin. When its
fin begins trembling rapidly, that means rain will
fall in a few hours.

135.name: Jolteon
135.info:
Rizza i peli e li scaglia come se fossero aghi.
Finisce gli avversari indeboliti con scariche da
10.000 volt.

136.name: Flareon
136.info:
The flame chamber inside its body ignites when
Flareon gets agitated, reaching temperatures of
up to 1,650 degrees Fahrenheit.

137.name: Porygon
137.info:
It was built 20 years ago by scientists who
dreamed of exploring space. Their dreams have
yet to come true.

138.name: Omanyte
138.info:
An ancient Pokémon that was recovered from
a fossil. It swam by cleverly twisting its
10 tentacles about.

139.name: Omastar
139.info:
Its sharp beak rings its mouth. Its shell was too
big for it to move freely, so it became extinct.

140.name: Kabuto
140.info:
A Pokémon that was recovered from a fossil.
It used the eyes on its back while hiding
on the seafloor.

141.name: Kabutops
141.info:
È un perfetto nuotatore. Taglia la preda
con le sue falci e ne succhia il sangue.

142.name: Aerodactyl
142.info:
It flew through the open skies over the ancient
continent as if they were its own. When it
touched ground, its walk was weak and slow.

143.name: Snorlax
143.info:
It has no interest in anything other than eating.
Even if you climb up on its stomach while it’s
napping, it doesn’t seem to mind at all!

144.name: Articuno
144.info:
This Pokémon can control ice at will. Articuno
is said to live in snowy mountains riddled
with permafrost.

145.name: Zapdos
145.info:
Zapdos is a legendary bird Pokémon. It’s said
that when Zapdos rubs its feathers together,
lightning will fall immediately after.

146.name: Moltres
146.info:
There are stories of this Pokémon using its
radiant, flame-cloaked wings to light up paths
for those lost in the mountains.

147.name: Dratini
147.info:
It sheds its skin—almost on a daily basis—and
grows larger. Its skin is soft just after it’s
been shed.

148.name: Dragonair
148.info:
Some say that if you see it at the start of the
year, flying through the sky and twisting its
body, you’ll be healthy all year long.

149.name: Dragonite
149.info:
You’ll often hear tales of this kindhearted
Pokémon rescuing people or Pokémon that
are drowning.

169.name: Crobat
169.info:
りょうあしが　ハネに　へんか。
おとを　たてずに　こうそくで　とび
エモノの　うなじに　キバを　たてる。

170.name: Chinchou
170.info:
ひれが　へんかして　できた
しょくしゅは　それぞれ　プラスと
マイナスの　でんきが　ながれている。

171.name: Lanturn
171.info:
ランターンのだす　ひかりは
５０００メートルの　ふかさ　からでも
すいめんまで　とどくほど　あかるい。

172.name: Pichu
172.info:
ちいさくても　おとなを　ビリビリ
させるほどの　でんげきを　はなてる。
ただし　じぶんも　おどろいてしまう。

173.name: Cleffa
173.info:
ピィを　よく　みかける　ばしょは
ながれぼしが　おちた　ばしょと
じもとでは　うわさ　されている。

174.name: Igglybuff
174.info:
うたを　うたうことが　だいすき。
マシュマロのような　からだからは
ほんのり　あまい　においが　するぞ。

185.name: Sudowoodo
185.info:
かぜも　ないのに　ゆれている　きを
みかけたら　それが　ウソッキー。
あめのひは　すがたを　かくすという。

186.name: Politoed
186.info:
よるになると　いけの　ほとりに
あらわれる。　どなるような　こえで
ないて　ナワバリを　アピールするぞ。

196.name: Espeon
196.info:
くうきの　ながれを　よみとることで
これからの　てんきや　あいての
うごきなどを　すべて　あててしまう。

197.name: Umbreon
197.info:
おこると　ぜんしんの　けあなから
どくその　まじった　あせを　ふきだし
あいての　めを　ねらう。

199.name: Slowking
199.info:
シェルダーの　どくそが　ヤドンの
のうみそを　かけめぐり　きせきてきに
ひめた　ちのうを　かくせいさせた。

212.name: Scizor
212.info:
おおきな　ハサミは　たいじゅうの
３ぶんの１の　おもさ。　ふりおろせば
がんせきも　いっぱつで　こなごなだ。

215.name: Sneasel
215.info:
会趁着夜色袭击猎物。
伸出爪子袭击穿山鼠时，有时会因
对方坚硬的皮肤而导致爪子折断。

222.name: Corsola
222.info:
あたまに　はえた　えだは　おれても
また　はえてくる。　きれいな　ものは
あんざんの　おまもりに　されるよ。

225.name: Delibird
225.info:
１にち　ずっと　エサをはこんでる。
そうなんした　ひとが　デリバードの
エサで　たすかった　はなしもある。

227.name: Skarmory
227.info:
するどい　ハネは　つるぎに　まさる
きれあじ。　ナワバリを　めぐって
アーマーガアと　はげしく　あらそう。

233.name: Porygon2
233.info:
ポリゴンを　とくべつな　データで
アップデート。　さまざまな　ことを
じぶんで　まなび　せいちょうする。

239.name: Elekid
239.info:
あらしが　ちかづくと　おちつきが
なくなる。　かみなりの　おとが
きこえると　たまらず　さわぎだす。

240.name: Magby
240.info:
まだまだ　ちいさく　おくびょう。
こうふんしたり　びっくりすると
はなや　くちから　ひが　もれる。

241.name: Miltank
241.info:
えいよう　まんてんの　ミルクを　だす
ことから　ふるくから　にんげんと
ポケモンの　くらしを　ささえてきた。

242.name: Blissey
242.info:
よわった　ポケモンを　みつけると
じぶんの　タマゴを　わけあたえ
なおるまで　かんびょうを　つづける。

278.name: Wingull
278.info:
Il construit son nid le long des falaises et utilise
les courants ascendants pour planer en altitude.

279.name: Pelipper
279.info:
くちのなかに　ちいさなポケモンや
タマゴをいれて　あんぜんな　ばしょに
とどけてくれる　そらの　はこびや。

302.name: Sableye
302.info:
Beaucoup de gens le craignent, car l’éclat
de ses yeux précieux donne l’impression qu’il
s’apprête à dérober l’âme de ceux qu’il regarde.

318.name: Carvanha
318.info:
Il ne s’attaque jamais à une proie tout seul,
préférant attendre l’arrivée de ses congénères
pour lancer l’assaut.

319.name: Sharpedo
319.info:
Dès qu’il détecte l’odeur d’une proie, il fonce
sur elle à une vitesse de 120 km/h en propulsant
de l’eau de mer par son postérieur.

320.name: Wailmer
320.info:
Il aime faire le beau en recrachant par son évent
l’eau qu’il a avalée.
Il gobe une tonne de Froussardine chaque jour.

321.name: Wailord
321.info:
L’énorme fracas causé par ses sauts par-dessus
les vagues peut faire perdre connaissance
à ses adversaires.

324.name: Torkoal
324.info:
Il tire son énergie du charbon qu’il brûle
dans sa carapace, et crache de la suie noire
en cas de danger.

328.name: Trapinch
328.info:
Il est impossible de s’échapper de son antre
en forme de cône qu’il creuse dans le sable
du désert.

329.name: Vibrava
329.info:
Ses violents battements d’ailes génèrent
des vagues d’ultrasons qui donnent
des migraines intenses.

330.name: Flygon
330.info:
Comme il est souvent caché au cœur des
tempêtes de sable qu’il déclenche, ce Pokémon
n’est que rarement aperçu par l’Homme.

339.name: Barboach
339.info:
Son corps glissant est difficile à attraper.
Dans une certaine région, on raconte qu’il est né
à partir de boue solidifiée.

340.name: Whiscash
340.info:
Il fait son nid au fond des marais.
Il ne se pose pas de question et avale
toutes les créatures qui passent près de lui.

349.name: Feebas
349.info:
Comme il est tout de même franchement laid,
ce Pokémon a un succès très mitigé. Sa grande
vitalité fait néanmoins l’objet de moult études.

350.name: Milotic
350.info:
Célébré comme l’un des plus beaux Pokémon,
il sert souvent de modèle et d’inspiration
aux plus grands artistes.

359.name: Absol
359.info:
Il court par monts et par vaux, rapide comme
le vent. Sa corne arquée lui permet de percevoir
les signes avant-coureurs des cataclysmes.

361.name: Snorunt
361.info:
Quand ce Pokémon apparaît la nuit, il provoque
de fortes chutes de neige.
Il se nourrit de glace et de neige.

362.name: Glalie
362.info:
Son corps constitué de glace ne peut pas fondre,
même s’il est exposé au feu. Il peut geler
l’humidité contenue dans l’air instantanément.

369.name: Relicanth
369.info:
Il peut supporter la pression des profondeurs
grâce à ses écailles aussi solides que le roc et
à ses vessies natatoires remplies de graisse.

371.name: Bagon
371.info:
Tous les jours, il se jette du haut d’une falaise
pour renforcer son corps, dans l’espoir de
pouvoir voler un jour.

372.name: Shelgon
372.info:
用成分與骨頭相同的硬殼
覆蓋身體。體內蓄積著
進化所需的能量。

373.name: Salamence
373.info:
Ce Pokémon rare a tellement souhaité
voler qu’il s’est vu pousser des ailes
pendant son évolution.

374.name: Beldum
374.info:
Ce Pokémon peut créer un champ magnétique
derrière lui qui attire ses ennemis avec force.
Il les embroche alors de ses griffes acérées.

375.name: Metang
375.info:
Composé de deux Terhal réunis par l’attraction
magnétique, ce Pokémon a vu sa puissance
psychique doubler grâce aux deux cerveaux.

376.name: Metagross
376.info:
Les Métalosse vivant sur des pics enneigés sont
très actifs, car leur force magnétique augmente
lorsque la température est inférieure à zéro.

422.name: Shellos
422.info:
環境で　姿が　変わる。
水温が　温かい　海では
この姿に　なるという　説も。

423.name: Gastrodon
423.info:
エサを　求めて　陸にも　上がる。
トリトドンが　這った跡には
ネバネバの　粘液が　残る。

425.name: Drifloon
425.info:
仲間が　欲しいのか　子どもに
近づくが　いいように　遊ばれ
逃げていくことも　少なくない。

426.name: Drifblim
426.info:
無念の　死を　とげた　魂が
集まった　姿とも　いわれる。
宵闇を　音も　なく　漂う。

438.name: Bonsly
438.info:
汗と　涙を　目から　流す。
汗は　ちょっぴり　しょっぱくて
涙は　ほんのり　苦い　味だ。

440.name: Happiny
440.info:
ラッキーの　真似をして　タマゴに
そっくりな　まるい　石を　お腹の
袋に　入れて　大事にしている。

443.name: Gible
443.info:
地熱で　暖められた　洞窟の
狭い　横穴を　好む。　外が
吹雪いていても　凍えずにすむのだ。

444.name: Gabite
444.info:
頭の　左右の　突起から
超音波を　出して　真っ暗な
洞穴の　様子を　調べるのだ。

445.name: Garchomp
445.info:
火山性の　山に　すみつく。
ジェット機に　負けない　速さで
空を　飛び　獲物を　狩りまくる。

446.name: Munchlax
446.info:
とにかく　たくさん　食べることに
夢中。　味も　気にしないし
腐っていても　平気　なのだ。

447.name: Riolu
447.info:
一晩中　走っていられる
スタミナを　もつ。　活発で
散歩の　相手は　たいへん。

448.name: Lucario
448.info:
大岩も　粉々に　砕く
波動と　呼ばれる　力を
操って　獲物を　狩る。

461.name: Weavile
461.info:
群れを　成し　獲物を　襲う。
チームプレーで　マンムーなどの
大物も　たやすく　しとめる。

462.name: Magnezone
462.info:
頭の　アンテナで　宇宙からの
電波を　受信して　何者かに
コントロールされていると　いわれる。

466.name: Electivire
466.info:
発電量は　心拍数と　比例する。
戦いになると　一気に
ボルテージが　上がるのだ。

467.name: Magmortar
467.info:
大きく　息を　吸いこむと　腹の
中の　炎が　勢いを　増して
摂氏２０００度に　達する。

470.name: Leafeon
470.info:
葉っぱから　漂う　クセのある
香りは　ガラル人の　好み。
香水に　加工され　人気。

471.name: Glaceon
471.info:
ダイヤモンドダストを　降らせる。
美しさに　見惚れた　獲物は
気づかぬうちに　凍りついている。

474.name: Porygon-z
474.info:
異次元　空間に　出入りできる
プログラムを　追加したところ
挙動が　不安定になった。

478.name: Froslass
478.info:
雪山で　亡くなった　女の
無念から　生まれた　ポケモン。
凍らせた　魂が　好物。

506.name: Lillipup
506.info:
Ce Pokémon est plus intelligent que la plupart
des enfants. Il n’oublie ni l’affection qu’il a reçue
ni les mauvais traitements qu’il a pu subir.

507.name: Herdier
507.info:
Les poils sombres qui recouvrent son dos sont
si épais et si souples qu’ils peuvent même
repousser des crocs acérés.

508.name: Stoutland
508.info:
Sa moustache remarquable fait sa fierté,
car sa longueur permettrait de déterminer
la hiérarchie au sein de l’espèce.

524.name: Roggenrola
524.info:
Il se déplace en réagissant aux sons environnants.
Son noyau d’énergie rend son corps légèrement
chaud au toucher.

525.name: Boldore
525.info:
Il sonde les environs grâce au son. Lorsqu’un
importun le met en colère, il se lance à sa
poursuite sans changer l’orientation de son corps.

526.name: Gigalith
526.info:
Il est capable d’envoyer des boules d’énergie
assez puissantes pour balayer un camion-benne,
mais il ne peut tirer que les jours ensoleillés.

546.name: Cottonee
546.info:
Les marques de luxe utilisent les étoffes
splendides issues du mélange des cotons
de Doudouvet et de Blancoton.

547.name: Whimsicott
547.info:
Son coton se met à gonfler sous les rayons
du soleil. Quand il est trop volumineux,
il s’effiloche et se répand aux alentours.

548.name: Petilil
548.info:
Plus ses feuilles sont foncées, plus il est en
bonne santé. Il s’installe parfois dans les champs
ou les parterres de fleurs bien entretenus.

549.name: Lilligant
549.info:
L’huile essentielle extraite de sa fleur dégage
un parfum exceptionnel, mais elle coûte
extrêmement cher.

551.name: Sandile
551.info:
Malgré son petit gabarit, il a beaucoup de force
dans les pattes arrière. Il parcourt le désert
comme s’il nageait dans le sable.

552.name: Krokorok
552.info:
Bien que ses yeux particuliers lui permettent
de voir dans l’obscurité, les nuits sont si froides
dans le désert qu’il ne se déplace presque pas.

553.name: Krookodile
553.info:
Il aime la violence, mais sait aussi se montrer
patient lorsqu’il doit passer plusieurs jours
dans le sable à attendre une proie.

564.name: Tirtouga
564.info:
Ancêtre présumé de nombreuses espèces
de Pokémon tortues, il a été restauré à partir
d’un fossile.

565.name: Carracosta
565.info:
Bien qu’il soit moins à l’aise sur terre que dans
l’eau, il s’aventure sur le rivage pour se nourrir.

566.name: Archen
566.info:
On dit que c’est l’ancêtre des Pokémon oiseaux.
Il vivait à la cime des arbres et se nourrissait de
Baies et de Pokémon Insecte.

567.name: Archeops
567.info:
Il savait voler, mais il semble qu’il était beaucoup
plus doué pour chasser ses proies sur la terre
ferme.

568.name: Trubbish
568.info:
Il est né d’un sac poubelle rempli d’ordures.
Le gaz empoisonné qu’il exhale est très apprécié
des Smogogo de Galar.

569.name: Garbodor
569.info:
Le liquide qu’il projette de son bras droit
est si toxique que si une créature fragile
en est aspergée, elle succombe sur-le-champ.

582.name: Vanillite
582.info:
On raconte qu’il est né de stalactites.
Il gèle les alentours en soufflant de l’air à - 50 °C
pour améliorer son confort.

583.name: Vanillish
583.info:
Bien qu’il gèle ses ennemis en soufflant de l’air
à - 100 °C, sa gentillesse l’empêche de leur ôter
la vie.

584.name: Vanilluxe
584.info:
La température de son corps est d’environ
- 6 °C. On raconte que ce Pokémon naît
lorsque deux Sorboul se collent l’un à l’autre.

587.name: Emolga
587.info:
Les Baies sucrées sont son péché mignon.
Il lui arrive d’en conserver beaucoup trop dans
ses bajoues, ce qui l’empêche de bien planer.

627.name: Rufflet
627.info:
Sa poigne est telle qu’il peut réduire en miettes
les plus dures des Baies. Belliqueux de nature,
il n’hésite pas à défier tout le monde.

628.name: Braviary
628.info:
Son caractère agressif et violent lui a valu
de perdre son rôle de transporteur à Galar
au profit de Corvaillus.

629.name: Vullaby
629.info:
Il grandit vite. Au sein du nid, les petits Vostourno
héritent des couches en crâne de leurs aînés.

630.name: Mandibuzz
630.info:
Il se pare d’ossements qu’il a ramassés.
Il semblerait qu’il choisisse la forme des os
qu’il porte selon les dernières tendances.

661.name: Fletchling
661.info:
一旦兴奋体温就会
急剧上升。赤手去摸
甚至有可能会被灼伤。

662.name: Fletchinder
662.info:
领地意识很强，性格好战。
火箭雀彼此之间会为了
觅食的地方发生争斗。

663.name: Talonflame
663.info:
会以５００公里的时速进行突击。
不给猎物留下逃跑的机会，
直接以猛烈的踢击将其解决。

674.name: Pancham
674.info:
为了不被小看而一直瞪着对手，
然而绷紧的神经一旦稍有放松，
它就会在无意中露出笑脸。

675.name: Pangoro
675.info:
通过叶子来洞悉敌人的动向。
只要使出一记拳击就能
让大型翻斗车变成废铁。

700.name: Sylveon
700.info:
伽勒尔地区的童话中有着
美丽的仙子伊布击退了
可怕的龙宝可梦的故事。

703.name: Carbink
703.info:
据说在世界上的某处，有个
沉睡着许多小碎钻的矿脉，
它们的女王也在那里。

704.name: Goomy
704.info:
它的触角是优秀的感觉器官。
只要感觉到有敌人就会立刻
藏起来，以此存活到了现在。

705.name: Sliggoo
705.info:
背上的突起物里装着它
小小的脑子，里面只想着
吃饭和逃离敌人这两件事。

706.name: Goodra
706.info:
用伸长角产生的力道来
攻击对手，产生的威力比
重量级拳击手的拳击还强１００倍。

707.name: Klefki
707.info:
会用头的前端吸取金属离子。
之所以长得像钥匙，据说是因为
太过喜欢钥匙，情不自禁进行了模仿。

708.name: Phantump
708.info:
用类似人类小孩的声音鸣叫，
把大人引到森林的深处，
让他们在其中迷失方向。

709.name: Trevenant
709.info:
脚尖伸出来的根须
能连结森林中的树木，
并且自由自在地加以操纵。

10001.name: Deoxys-attack
alt: ディフェンスフォルム

10033.name: Venusaur-mega
10033.info:
A bewitching aroma wafts from its flower.
The fragrance becalms those engaged
in a battle.

10034.name: Charizard-mega-x
10034.info:
Its wings can carry this Pokémon close to an
altitude of 4,600 feet. It blows out fire at very
high temperatures.

10035.name: Charizard-mega-y
10035.info:
Its wings can carry this Pokémon close to an
altitude of 4,600 feet. It blows out fire at very
high temperatures.

10036.name: Blastoise-mega
10036.info:
The rocket cannons on its shell fire jets of water
capable of punching holes through thick steel.

10037.name: Alakazam-mega
10037.info:
If it trusts someone deeply, it will let them have
one of its spoons. Anything you eat with that
spoon is apparently delicious.

10038.name: Gengar-mega
10038.info:
Even your home isn’t safe. Gengar will lurk in
whatever dark corner of a room it can find and
wait for its chance to catch its prey.

10039.name: Kangaskhan-mega
10039.info:
Non bisogna avvicinarsi a un cucciolo che gioca
fuori dal marsupio: la madre è sempre nei
paraggi e vigila attenta su di lui.

10040.name: Pinsir-mega
10040.info:
Although it’s tough, it can’t handle cold well.
When night falls, it buries itself in leafage
and sleeps.

10041.name: Gyarados-mega
10041.info:
The energy from evolution stimulated its brain
cells strongly, causing it to become
very ferocious.

10042.name: Aerodactyl-mega
10042.info:
It flew through the open skies over the ancient
continent as if they were its own. When it
touched ground, its walk was weak and slow.

10046.name: Scizor-mega
10046.info:
おおきな　ハサミは　たいじゅうの
３ぶんの１の　おもさ。　ふりおろせば
がんせきも　いっぱつで　こなごなだ。

10057.name: Absol-mega
10057.info:
Il court par monts et par vaux, rapide comme
le vent. Sa corne arquée lui permet de percevoir
les signes avant-coureurs des cataclysmes.

10058.name: Garchomp-mega
10058.info:
火山性の　山に　すみつく。
ジェット機に　負けない　速さで
空を　飛び　獲物を　狩りまくる。

10059.name: Lucario-mega
10059.info:
大岩も　粉々に　砕く
波動と　呼ばれる　力を
操って　獲物を　狩る。

10066.name: Sableye-mega
10066.info:
Beaucoup de gens le craignent, car l’éclat
de ses yeux précieux donne l’impression qu’il
s’apprête à dérober l’âme de ceux qu’il regarde.

10070.name: Sharpedo-mega
10070.info:
Dès qu’il détecte l’odeur d’une proie, il fonce
sur elle à une vitesse de 120 km/h en propulsant
de l’eau de mer par son postérieur.

10071.name: Slowbro-mega
10071.info:
Shellder, in its greed to suck out more and more
sweetness from Slowbro’s tail, has
metamorphosed into a spiral-shaped shell.

10074.name: Glalie-mega
10074.info:
Son corps constitué de glace ne peut pas fondre,
même s’il est exposé au feu. Il peut geler
l’humidité contenue dans l’air instantanément.

10076.name: Metagross-mega
10076.info:
Les Métalosse vivant sur des pics enneigés sont
très actifs, car leur force magnétique augmente
lorsque la température est inférieure à zéro.
alt: ゲンシカイキのすがた

10077.name: Kyogre-primal
alt: ゲンシカイキのすがた

10080.name: Pikachu-rock-star
10080.info:
While sleeping, it generates electricity in the
sacs in its cheeks. If it’s not getting enough
sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.

10081.info:
While sleeping, it generates electricity in the
sacs in its cheeks. If it’s not getting enough
sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.

10082.info:
While sleeping, it generates electricity in the
sacs in its cheeks. If it’s not getting enough
sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.

10083.info:
While sleeping, it generates electricity in the
sacs in its cheeks. If it’s not getting enough
sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.

10084.name: Pikachu-libre
10084.info:
While sleeping, it generates electricity in the
sacs in its cheeks. If it’s not getting enough
sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.

10085.name: Pikachu-cosplay
10085.info:
While sleeping, it generates electricity in the
sacs in its cheeks. If it’s not getting enough
sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.
alt: ときはなたれしフーパ

10089.name: Salamence-mega
10089.info:
Ce Pokémon rare a tellement souhaité
voler qu’il s’est vu pousser des ailes
pendant son évolution.

10091.name: Rattata-alola
10091.info:
Un Pokémon muy extendido con el que conviene
tener cuidado ya que sus afilados incisivos son
capaces de roer maderas nobles sin problema.

10092.name: Raticate-alola
10092.info:
Its whiskers are essential for maintaining its
balance. No matter how friendly you are, it will
get angry and bite you if you touch its whiskers.

10093.name: Raticate-totem-alola
10093.info:
Its whiskers are essential for maintaining its
balance. No matter how friendly you are, it will
get angry and bite you if you touch its whiskers.

10094.name: Pikachu-original-cap
10094.info:
While sleeping, it generates electricity in the
sacs in its cheeks. If it’s not getting enough
sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.

10095.name: Pikachu-hoenn-cap
10095.info:
While sleeping, it generates electricity in the
sacs in its cheeks. If it’s not getting enough
sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.

10096.name: Pikachu-sinnoh-cap
10096.info:
While sleeping, it generates electricity in the
sacs in its cheeks. If it’s not getting enough
sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.

10097.name: Pikachu-unova-cap
10097.info:
While sleeping, it generates electricity in the
sacs in its cheeks. If it’s not getting enough
sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.

10098.name: Pikachu-kalos-cap
10098.info:
While sleeping, it generates electricity in the
sacs in its cheeks. If it’s not getting enough
sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.

10099.name: Pikachu-alola-cap
10099.info:
While sleeping, it generates electricity in the
sacs in its cheeks. If it’s not getting enough
sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.

10100.name: Raichu-alola
10100.info:
Because so many Trainers like the way Pikachu
looks, you don’t see this Pokémon very often.

10101.name: Sandshrew-alola
10101.info:
When its skin gets wrinkled from moisture, it
heads for a volcano. It lies flat on a spot with a
lot of geothermal heat and dries itself out.

10102.name: Sandslash-alola
10102.info:
Thanks to its thick claws, it’s good at climbing
trees. There are plenty of Sandslash that park
themselves in trees and go right to sleep.

10103.name: Vulpix-alola
10103.info:
Crea palle infuocate che usa con maestria per
catturare le prede. Se allenato fin da cucciolo,
si affeziona come un Pokémon Cagnolino.

10104.name: Ninetales-alola
10104.info:
The flickering flames it spews from its mouth
leave its opponents hypnotized. Then, this
extremely intelligent Pokémon attacks.

10105.name: Diglett-alola
10105.info:
Around their crops, farmers plant the kind of
tree that Diglett like to eat as a way of getting
Diglett to plow the fields for them.

10106.name: Dugtrio-alola
10106.info:
Dugtrio’s heads are sleek and smooth and
incredibly hard. It can dig through any soil with
its headbutts.

10107.name: Meowth-alola
10107.info:
It loves coins, so if you give it one, you can
make friends with Meowth easily. But it’s fickle,
so you can’t count on that friendship lasting.

10108.name: Persian-alola
10108.info:
Un Pokémon de alto copete, objetivo primordial
de ladrones que quieren apoderarse de la joya
que luce en la frente.

10109.name: Geodude-alola
10109.info:
It uses both hands to climb precipitous cliffs.
People who see it in action have been known to
take up bouldering.

10110.name: Graveler-alola
10110.info:
Si sposta rotolando lungo dirupi scoscesi.
Se finisce dentro a un fiume, viene colto dalla
disperazione e si fa esplodere.

10111.name: Golem-alola
10111.info:
It detonates its own body. The power from
that explosion can propel it up steep mountain
paths with amazing speed.

10112.name: Grimer-alola
10112.info:
The wastewater coming from factories is clean
these days, so Grimer have nothing to eat.
They’re said to be on the verge of extinction.

10113.name: Muk-alola
10113.info:
Essendo portatore di germi, è stato sempre
cacciato senza pietà. Per questo il numero di
esemplari si è ridotto drasticamente.

10114.name: Exeggutor-alola
10114.info:
Each of its three heads has its own thoughts.
When they want to go in different directions,
Exeggutor becomes unable to move.

10115.name: Marowak-alola
10115.info:
They thump their bones rhythmically to
communicate among themselves. There are
nearly 50 different rhythmic patterns.

10119.name: Zygarde-50-power-construct
alt: パーフェクトフォルム

10147.name: Magearna-original
alt: キミにきめたキャップ

10148.name: Pikachu-partner-cap
10148.info:
While sleeping, it generates electricity in the
sacs in its cheeks. If it’s not getting enough
sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.

10149.name: Marowak-totem
10149.info:
They thump their bones rhythmically to
communicate among themselves. There are
nearly 50 different rhythmic patterns.

10158.name: Pikachu-starter
10158.info:
While sleeping, it generates electricity in the
sacs in its cheeks. If it’s not getting enough
sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.

10159.name: Eevee-starter
10159.info:
Its genes are easily influenced by its
surroundings. Even its face starts to look like
that of its Trainer.

10160.name: Pikachu-world-cap
10160.info:
While sleeping, it generates electricity in the
sacs in its cheeks. If it’s not getting enough
sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.

10161.name: Meowth-galar
10161.info:
It loves coins, so if you give it one, you can
make friends with Meowth easily. But it’s fickle,
so you can’t count on that friendship lasting.

10162.name: Ponyta-galar
10162.info:
If you’ve been accepted by Ponyta, its burning
mane is mysteriously no longer hot to the touch.

10163.name: Rapidash-galar
10163.info:
The fastest runner becomes the leader, and it
decides the herd’s pace and direction of travel.

10164.name: Slowpoke-galar
10164.info:
Although their tails, which fall off naturally, can
easily be found lying around, they’re a precious
ingredient for cooking.

10165.name: Slowbro-galar
10165.info:
Shellder, in its greed to suck out more and more
sweetness from Slowbro’s tail, has
metamorphosed into a spiral-shaped shell.

10166.name: Farfetchd-galar
10166.info:
They use a plant stalk as a weapon, but not all
of them use it in the same way. Several distinct
styles of stalk fighting have been observed.

10167.name: Weezing-galar
10167.info:
It can’t suck in air quite as well as a Galarian
Weezing, but the toxins it creates are more
potent than those of its counterpart.

10168.name: Mr-mime-galar
10168.info:
Always practicing its pantomime act.
It makes enemies believe something exists
that really doesn’t.

10169.name: Articuno-galar
10169.info:
This Pokémon can control ice at will. Articuno
is said to live in snowy mountains riddled
with permafrost.

10170.name: Zapdos-galar
10170.info:
Zapdos is a legendary bird Pokémon. It’s said
that when Zapdos rubs its feathers together,
lightning will fall immediately after.

10171.name: Moltres-galar
10171.info:
There are stories of this Pokémon using its
radiant, flame-cloaked wings to light up paths
for those lost in the mountains.

10172.name: Slowking-galar
10172.info:
シェルダーの　どくそが　ヤドンの
のうみそを　かけめぐり　きせきてきに
ひめた　ちのうを　かくせいさせた。

10173.name: Corsola-galar
10173.info:
あたまに　はえた　えだは　おれても
また　はえてくる。　きれいな　ものは
あんざんの　おまもりに　されるよ。

10195.name: Venusaur-gmax
10195.info:
A bewitching aroma wafts from its flower.
The fragrance becalms those engaged
in a battle.

10196.name: Charizard-gmax
10196.info:
Its wings can carry this Pokémon close to an
altitude of 4,600 feet. It blows out fire at very
high temperatures.

10197.name: Blastoise-gmax
10197.info:
The rocket cannons on its shell fire jets of water
capable of punching holes through thick steel.

10198.name: Butterfree-gmax
10198.info:
Nectar from pretty flowers is its favorite food.
In fields of flowers, it has heated battles with
Cutiefly for territory.

10199.name: Pikachu-gmax
10199.info:
While sleeping, it generates electricity in the
sacs in its cheeks. If it’s not getting enough
sleep, it will be able to use only weak electricity.

10200.name: Meowth-gmax
10200.info:
It loves coins, so if you give it one, you can
make friends with Meowth easily. But it’s fickle,
so you can’t count on that friendship lasting.

10201.name: Machamp-gmax
10201.info:
Grazie alle sue quattro braccia può attaccare
e difendersi allo stesso tempo. Si dice che sia
esperto di tutte le arti marziali del mondo.

10202.name: Gengar-gmax
10202.info:
Even your home isn’t safe. Gengar will lurk in
whatever dark corner of a room it can find and
wait for its chance to catch its prey.

10203.name: Kingler-gmax
10203.info:
Its oversized claw is very powerful, but when it’s
not in battle, the claw just gets in the way.

10204.name: Lapras-gmax
10204.info:
They’ve been so cherished that there’s now an
overabundance. The fish Pokémon population
has declined in waters with too many Lapras.

10205.name: Eevee-gmax
10205.info:
Its genes are easily influenced by its
surroundings. Even its face starts to look like
that of its Trainer.

10206.name: Snorlax-gmax
10206.info:
It has no interest in anything other than eating.
Even if you climb up on its stomach while it’s
napping, it doesn’t seem to mind at all!

10207.name: Garbodor-gmax
10207.info:
Le liquide qu’il projette de son bras droit
est si toxique que si une créature fragile
en est aspergée, elle succombe sur-le-champ.
